review_blob: 50cl bottle in Cerveceria Arte&Sana; Malaga. Black, thin head. Lovely aroma, licorice, malt, sweetness, roastedness. Flavor has roasted malt, licorice, burnt notes, hops. Finish is dry, long, with licorice and coffee notes. Wonderfull.
Bottle in Cerveceria Arte&Sana; Mlaga. Hazy golden body, large white head. Tons of hops, grass, grapefruit, fruit, tropical fruit, malt, light caramel notes. Heavy bitter, dry. Delicious ipa.
De barril en Cerveceria Arte&Sana;, una Ipa muy buena, aromatica, con aromas y sabores a fruta tropical y hierba fresca. Muy buena

Pours hazy golden orang, white head, leaves some lacing on the glass. Fruity aroma (citrus, pineapple, some tropical note). Taste is malts with fruity notes similar to the nose, dry finish with bitter grassy hoppy notes. Medium body, medium carbonation. Very drinkable and enjoyable hoppy lager.
Rich, sweet and bitter taste. aroma too beautiful! Bitterness on the palate is long. Very nice beer.
pours cloudy amber with a thick off-white head and a fruity aroma. There is a full-bodied toffee and citrus flavor with a bitter finish.
